  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle and add the <strong>boiled water</strong> to a pot with a pinch of <strong>salt<strong>&nbsp;</strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>lasagne verdi sheets</strong>,&nbsp;one at a time,&nbsp;with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> between each one (this stops them sticking together)</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 12 min or until they have softened&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat&nbsp;a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1-2 tbsp <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;hot, add the<strong> chopped&nbsp;carrot</strong> and cook for 30 sec&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>beef mince</strong>, break it up with a wooden spoon and cook for a further 30 sec</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped&nbsp;garlic</strong> and cook for a further 3 min, or until the meat is no longer pink</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crumble the<strong>&nbsp;beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into the <strong>beef mince</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, 1/2 tsp&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1&nbsp;tsp]</span><strong>&nbsp;sugar</strong> and the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for a further 4 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>chestnut&nbsp;mushrooms</strong> into quarters</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add approx. 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span>&nbsp;of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> (that your lasagne sheets are cooking in) to the <strong>mince</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped&nbsp;mushrooms</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for a further 5 min or until the mushrooms are tender and the sauce has thickened</p>\r\n<p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> &ndash;&nbsp;this is your<strong> ragu</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop (or tear)&nbsp;the<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Grate the&nbsp;<strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Check the <strong>lasagne verdi sheets</strong> are cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot with a little<strong>&nbsp;starchy pasta water</strong> (this prevents them from sticking together)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/rich-open-beef-lasagne-with-basil/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, place a <strong>lasagne sheet</strong> on each plate and spoon over some of the <strong>ragu</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle some <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped basil</strong> over, then repeat with the remaining <strong>lasagne sheets</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
